cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with interval temporal logic and its application in model checking. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as model checking is a widely used method in formal verification, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the model checking problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with the formalization of the model checking problem in an interval logic setting, which can be seen as a programming language. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as model checking is a technique used in software engineering for verifying software systems.
